html += """<p id="text-bio" class="text-component instance-1" style="text-align: left; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.75; font-weight: 400; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85); margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">I’m an adventure-driven filmmaker and educator whose work grows out of being on the ground, walking mountain routes, scouting backstreets, filming in real locations, and building maps that connect cinematic storytelling to lived experience. I created Tokyo in Film and its ongoing location project, documenting shrines, rail lines, neighborhoods, coastlines, and historical sites across Japan. My videography ranges from action choreography with local stunt teams to travel films and cultural fieldwork. I’ve carried this approach across more than thirty countries over three passports, letting each place shape the way I frame what I see. If you would like to hire me for professional planning or as an on-site guide, I can provide travel itineraries for places you may not otherwise find and/or full logistical planning. If you would like to hire me for videography or editing, please contact me below.</p>"""
html += """<p id="text-collab" class="text-component instance-1" style="text-align: center; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 3rem;"><strong style="display: block; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Planning / Guide / Videography</strong><span style="font-family: 'Nunito Sans', sans-serif;">For local companies, organizations, and community groups that want to partner with me, I welcome opportunities to collaborate; please contact me! 地域の企業、団体、コミュニティの皆さまで私との協力をご希望の方はぜひご連絡ください!</span></p>"""
html += """<p id="text-partners-intro" class="text-component instance-2" style="font-size: 1.1em; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem;">Local Partners of Tokyo in Film:</p>"""
html += """<p id="text-donation" class="text-component instance-1" style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 3rem;">My work is built on authentic, location-based filmmaking and a commitment to helping my students understand places through direct experience. Most of the work I do is non-profit, including the textbooks that I write. Feel free to donate; all proceeds go to equipment or production for my students:</p>"""
